                  <div class="arrange-unit__09f24__rqHTg arrange-unit-fill__09f24__CUubG css-1qn0b6x">
                   <span class="css-chan6m">
                    Sep 15, 2023
                   </span>
                  </div>

                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <div class="css-1e7audd">
                  <div class="css-5d1n8n">
                   <span alt="" aria-hidden="true" class="icon--16-camera-v2 css-6a0jil" role="img">
                    <svg class="icon_svg" height="16" width="16">
                     <path d="M3.06 14.76a2.086 2.086 0 0 1-2.084-2.083V5.344A2.091 2.091 0 0 1 3.06 3.25h1.393l.496-1.487a.75.75 0 0 1 .711-.513h4.334a.75.75 0 0 1 .711.513l.496 1.487h1.74a2.086 2.086 0 0 1 2.083 2.083v7.334a2.086 2.086 0 0 1-2.084 2.083l-9.88.01Zm0-10.01a.59.59 0 0 0-.584.594v7.333a.584.584 0 0 0 .584.584l9.88-.011a.584.584 0 0 0 .584-.583V5.333a.584.584 0 0 0-.584-.583h-2.28a.75.75 0 0 1-.711-.513L9.453 2.75H6.201l-.496 1.487a.75.75 0 0 1-.711.513H3.06Z">
                     </path>
                     <path d="M8 12.556a3.75 3.75 0 1 1 0-7.501 3.75 3.75 0 0 1 0 7.5Zm0-6a2.25 2.25 0 1 0 0 4.5 2.25 2.25 0 0 0 0-4.5Z">
                     </path>
                    </svg>
                   </span>
                  </div>
                  <span class="css-1oibaro" data-font-weight="semibold">
                   <a class="css-19v1rkv" href="/biz_photos/milk-and-cream-cereal-bar-new-york?userid=u79JLmKzua7wxGxs1Q3Qkg">
                    2 photos
                   </a>
                  </span>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   Nostalgic ice cream creations, incorporating childhood favorite cereals into soft serve. The Lower East Side shop is colorful and cute, with digital signs displaying the various flavor combinations. Creations are blended to order, so you can craft your own flavors, or choose from their specials menu (recommended). If you've had a McFlurry or Dairy Queen Blizzard, this is similar, but better.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   An hour before closing, they were sold out of every special except the P-Nut Jelly Crumble. They also did not have the grape drizzle it comes with, but they were able to swap it for strawberry, which was likely just as good. There were no cones available either, but they did have cup cones, which ended up being a good move; these treats melt quickly!
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   On a weeknight in August, it took 30 minutes for my order to be completed. Fortunately, it was worth the wait. The P-Nut Jelly Crumble was delicious. I loved the muted peanut flavor of the Reese's Puffs blended into the creamy soft serve, and the crunch from the roasted peanuts and Reese's Pieces on top. Inventory issues aside, Milk &amp; Cream is a unique, well executed concept.
                  </span>
                 </p>
                </div>

                    <svg class="icon_svg" height="16" width="16">
                     <path d="M3.06 14.76a2.086 2.086 0 0 1-2.084-2.083V5.344A2.091 2.091 0 0 1 3.06 3.25h1.393l.496-1.487a.75.75 0 0 1 .711-.513h4.334a.75.75 0 0 1 .711.513l.496 1.487h1.74a2.086 2.086 0 0 1 2.083 2.083v7.334a2.086 2.086 0 0 1-2.084 2.083l-9.88.01Zm0-10.01a.59.59 0 0 0-.584.594v7.333a.584.584 0 0 0 .584.584l9.88-.011a.584.584 0 0 0 .584-.583V5.333a.584.584 0 0 0-.584-.583h-2.28a.75.75 0 0 1-.711-.513L9.453 2.75H6.201l-.496 1.487a.75.75 0 0 1-.711.513H3.06Z">

                   <a class="css-19v1rkv" href="/biz_photos/milk-and-cream-cereal-bar-new-york?userid=t9smvpIRq_--8NFFLrpi0g">
                    2 photos
                   </a>

                </div>
                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   Stumbled upon this place after my friend and I were craving some sweets after dinner in the Chinatown area. Not a huge soft serve person but surprisingly I really enjoyed this place! I got the cookie dough ice cream with cookie crisp (cereal option) and cookie dough pieces (topping) with a chocolate drizzle. It's cool to see them mixing and churning the ice cream with your cereal of choice. Liked how the soft serve was soft but didn't melt too quickly. Couldn't really taste the cookie dough flavor within the ice cream but I did like how the cereal gave it some crunch but wasn't soggy at all. Cookie dough pieces were pretty solid. The waffle cone almost tasted like generic cereal too and had some vanilla wafer vibes (as opposed to waffle cone). The portion was pretty big for a dessert!
                   <br/>
                   Good amount of seating available and everything was clean. Staff were polite!
                  </span>
                 </p>
                </div>

                   Typical ice cream joint, trying to put a unique spin on it by adding cereal as a main component of the toppings.

                   <br/>
                   Nothing tasted bad. Just didn't feel like it was anything special. $8.50 for a soft serve ice cream cup. If you love cereal and want to try it, go for it. Not sure if I'd go out of the way to get it

                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   I'm shocked by how much I loved my ice cream here. I think what got me was that I'm a sucker for a good blend. When ice cream places let me choose an ice cream and a topping and actually combine them to essentially make my own little creation, it GETS me, okay. (I'm looking at you, Thomas Sweet near Princeton... it has my heart)
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   But I didn't realize they did it here too! I thought it was just cereal with soft serve, but NO. They COMBINE them, baby. I ended up choosing one of their fixed menu options because I wanted something that was tested and good, so I went with their Banana Cream, which is an ice cream that has bananas and honey bunches of oats combined into one.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   I was a little terrified when I was handing over my money because this was a whopping $9.80, which is a little crazy, BUT for that $9.80 I got a HEFTY cup of ice cream. It's 100% shareable if you're getting a fixed menu item. My friend and I sat at a table for what felt like at least an hour as I savored each bite. The ice cream was smooth and the honey bunches added a great texture to it, AND went so well with the banana flavor they added.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   I would definitely come back and try more of their menu items and maybe even make my own lil creation next time!
                  </span>
                 </p>
                </div>

                   Interesting concept! My friends mentioned it a while back but I haven't gone till recently.                  <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   This may be my new favorite ice cream place! I ordered the Froot Berry Bliss, although I rarely opt for a fruity option when having ice cream. I loved it!! May seem pricey but it is a sizable portion. You could probably share with someone. I of course enjoyed the entire thing. They have several tables and seats at the bar, where you can watch the employees whip up the concoctions being ordered. It was nice being able to sit at the bar and not have to eat it in the heat.
                   <br/>
                   You also need to have some patience when you order. They blend the ice cream and cereal as it's ordered. Well with the wait!
                  </span>
                 </p>
                </div>

ice cream creations, incorporating childhood favorite cereals into soft serve. The Lower East Side shop is colorful and cute, with digital signs displaying the various flavor combinations. Creations are blended to order, so you can craft your own flavors, or choose from their specials menu (recommended). If you&#x27;ve had a McFlurry or Dairy Queen Blizzard, this is similar, but better. \n\nAn hour before closing, they were sold out of every special except the P-Nut Jelly Crumble. They also did not have the grape drizzle it comes with, but they were able to swap it for strawberry, which was likely just as good. ice cream creations, incorporating childhood favorite cereals into soft serve. The Lower East Side shop is colorful and cute, with digital signs displaying the various flavor combinations. Creations are blended to order, so you can craft your own flavors, or choose from their specials menu (recommended). If you&#x27;ve had a McFlurry or Dairy Queen Blizzard, this is similar, but better. \n\nAn hour before closing, they were sold out of every special except the P-Nut Jelly Crumble. They also did not have the grape drizzle it comes with, but they were able to swap it for strawberry, which was likely just as good. There were no cones available either, but they did have cup cones, which ended up being a good move; these treats melt quickly! \n\nOn a weeknight in August, it took 30 minutes for my order to be completed. Fortunately, it was worth the wait. The P-Nut Jelly Crumble was delicious. I loved the muted peanut flavor of the Reese&#x27;s Puffs blended into the creamy soft serve, and the crunch from the roasted peanuts and Reese&#x27;s Pieces on top. Inventory issues aside, Milk &amp; Cream is a unique, well executed
